claim.claim-text:
10. A method of providing participation over a computer network, the method comprises: 
submitting over the computer network an electronic order for an option contract by a participant into an automated execution system; 
receiving the electronic order over the computer network, wherein the electronic order is forwarded to a book process subsystem; 
executing the electronic order against a book order, if any; and 
assigning a first remaining portion of the electronic order to the participant.
